SUMMARY:Preparing to run biomolecular QM/MM simulations with CP2K using 
 AmberTools Online
UID:https://hpc-portal.eu/node/1470
DESCRIPTION:<p>This online course covers basic tools and technologies 
 needed to succeed in the setting up a QM/MM simulation with AmberTools 
 suite\, with hands-on exercises. It provides background to preparation of 
 biological systems for molecular modelling and practical experience in 
 successfully creating topologies and running simple QM/MM simulations 
 using CP2K in a HPC environment.</p> <p>The course uses examples drawn 
 from EPCC’s experiences in the life-sciences and HPC computing\, but using
  free tools and technologies commonly used in the biomolecular modelling 
 community. You will learn the intricacies of molecular modelling of 
 biological systems\, as well as practical aspects of handling and 
 preparing PDB files\, creating topologies ready to run using CP2K 
 softwares.</p> <p><strong>Audience:</strong> The course is aimed at 
 biomolecular modellers who want to use QM/MM simulations in their 
 work.</p>
LOCATION:https://bioexcel.eu/events/preparing-to-run-biomolecular-qm-mm-
 simulations-with-cp2k-using-ambertools-online/
DTSTAMP:20220830T140834Z
GEO:52.077917;0.187124
X-ALT-DESC;FMTTYPE=text/html:<!DOCTYPE HTML><HTML><BODY><p>This online 
 course covers basic tools and technologies needed to succeed in the 
 setting up a QM/MM simulation with AmberTools suite, with hands-on 
 exercises. It provides background to preparation of biological systems for
  molecular modelling and practical experience in successfully creating 
 topologies and running simple QM/MM simulations using CP2K in a HPC 
 environment.</p> <p>The course uses examples drawn from EPCC’s experiences
  in the life-sciences and HPC computing, but using free tools and 
 technologies commonly used in the biomolecular modelling community. You 
 will learn the intricacies of molecular modelling of biological systems, 
 as well as practical aspects of handling and preparing PDB files, creating
  topologies ready to run using CP2K softwares.</p> 
 <p><strong>Audience:</strong> The course is aimed at biomolecular 
 modellers who want to use QM/MM simulations in their 
 work.</p></BODY></HTML>
END:VEVENT
