SUMMARY:PATC: Short course on HPC-based Computational Bio-Medicine
UID:https://hpc-portal.eu/node/1484
DESCRIPTION:<h2>Objectives</h2> <p>The objetive of this course is to give a
  panorama on the use of hpc-based computational mechanics in Engineering 
 and Environment through the projects BSC are carrying on. This panorama 
 includes the basics of what is behind the main tools: computational 
 mechanics and parallelization. The training is delivered in collaboration 
 with the center of excellence CompBioMed.</p> <h2>Learning Outcomes</h2> 
 <p>The course gives a wide perspective and the latest trends of how HPC 
 helps in industrial\, clinical and research applications allowing to 
 achieve more realistic multiphysics simulations. In addition\, the student
  has the opportunity of running Jobs in Marenostrum supercomputer.</p>
LOCATION:https://events.prace-ri.eu/event/912/
DTSTAMP:20220830T140834Z
